The article discusses the calls made by Vice President Biden to Iraqi Prime Minister Nouri al-Maliki, Iraqi Speaker of Parliament Osama al-Nujaifi, and President of the Iraqi Kurdistan Region Masoud Barzani. The calls focused on the security situation in Iraq and the support being provided by the United States to Iraqi security forces in their fight against the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL). The Vice President stressed the need for national unity, coordination on security issues, and the formation of a new government under the constitution. He also emphasized the importance of embedding security measures within a broader strategy to enlist local communities in the fight against ISIL. The Vice President offered his sympathies for the killing and destruction in Speaker Nujaifi's home province and discussed mobilizing the population against ISIL. He also highlighted the importance of security coordination between Kurdish forces and Iraqi Security Forces and the role of the Kurds in the national political process. Lastly, the Vice President mentioned the participation of leaders from all national communities in Baghdad and their unanimous declaration of ISIL as an enemy of all Iraqis.